"title": "6734: repentance, importance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6734: repentance, importance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Repentance is of central importance because sin brings God's judgment and fellowship with God is only possible through full and sincere repentance. God, through his servants, calls people to repent as the only way to escape the judgment and receive the forgiveness and restoration which he offers.</p>\n<h2>The call to repentance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:32\">LUK 5:32</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:19-Jas5:20\">JAS 5:19–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:4-Jer25:6\">JER 25:4–25:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:7-Ezek33:9\">EZK 33:7–33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:4\">MRK 1:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3\">LUK 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">LUK 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24-2Tim2:26\">2TI 2:24–2:26</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance opens the way for blessing</h2>\n<h3>It is the only way to escape God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:30-Ezek18:32\">EZK 18:30–18:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:12\">JOB 36:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:7-Jer18:8\">JER 18:7–18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:3\">JER 26:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:5\">HOS 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:10\">JON 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8-Luke3:9\">LUK 3:8–3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:5\">REV 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>It prepares the way for God's kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:14-Mark1:15\">MRK 1:14–1:15</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:2\">MAT 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>It brings forgiveness and restoration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:13-2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:13–7:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:7\">ISA 55:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:1-Deut30:10\">DEU 30:1–30:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:8-Neh1:9\">NEH 1:8–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:23-Job22:25\">JOB 22:23–22:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:10-Job36:11\">JOB 36:10–36:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:22\">ISA 44:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38-Acts2:39\">ACT 2:38–2:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:19\">ACT 3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31\">ACT 5:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:18\">ACT 11:18</a></p>\n<h2>God desires that all people should repent</h2>\n<h3>He wants everyone to be saved</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:23\">EZK 18:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>His patience with the unrepentant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:2\">ISA 65:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:21\">REV 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>His discipline encourages repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:18-Jer31:20\">JER 31:18–31:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:20-Isa10:21\">ISA 10:20–10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:22\">ISA 19:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:6-Hos2:7\">HOS 2:6–2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:1\">HOS 6:1</a></p>\n<h2>Taking God's opportunity for repentance</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:6\">ISA 55:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:30-Acts17:31\">ACT 17:30–17:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13-Heb3:15\">HEB 3:13–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:7\">HEB 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7-Ps95:8\">PSA 95:7–95:8</a></p>\n<h2>Refusing God's opportunity for repentance</h2>\n<h3>Examples of those who refuse to repent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:15\">JER 35:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:3\">JER 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:20\">MAT 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:32\">MAT 21:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:20-Rev9:21\">REV 9:20–9:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:9-Rev16:11\">REV 16:9–16:11</a></p>\n<h3>God confirms those who refuse to repent in their hardness of heart</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:14-Matt13:15\">MAT 13:14–13:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:11–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:25-Acts28:27\">ACT 28:25–28:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:10\">ISA 6:10</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance may not remove the effects of human sin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:39-Num14:45\">NUM 14:39–14:45</a> <em>The Israelites' repentance could not prevent the wandering that resulted from their refusal to enter the promised land</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:24-1Sam15:26\">1SA 15:24–15:26</a> <em>Saul's repentance is too late to escape God's judgment on his kingship</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:13-2Sam12:14\">2SA 12:13–12:14</a> <em>Despite David's repentance the son of his adulterous relationship with Bathsheba still died</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16-Heb12:17\">HEB 12:16–12:17</a> <em>Esau's repentance could not bring back the birthright he had sold to Jacob.</em></p>",
